## Text rendering performance — the ShapePlan root cause

**Background — what `tracing` spans reveal and don't reveal:**

`ChatMessageView::render` is instrumented with a `trace_span!("chat_message::render", role, text_len, collapsed)` and `chat_panel::list_item` wraps the list render closure. These spans measure element-tree *construction* only — a few microseconds. GPUI's actual text-shaping cost happens later in `prepaint`, which runs after `render()` returns. The 500 ms scroll hitch will not appear inside these spans; it appears as *wall-clock silence* between successive span events. Enable with `RUST_LOG=u_forge_ui_gpui=trace`.

**How the hitch was diagnosed:**

1. `tracing` spans confirmed `render()` is fast (~10 µs); the 550 ms gap between consecutive `list_item` close events pointed squarely at GPUI's post-render pipeline.
2. `samply record cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui` + `RUST_LOG=off` during a scroll-in of a large message produced a flamegraph: **89 % of samples in `gpui::text_system::shape_text`**, **77 % in `rustybuzz::hb::ot_map::hb_ot_map_builder_t::compile` → `find_language_feature`**.
3. Root cause: `cosmic-text 0.14.2` calls `rustybuzz::ShapePlan::new(...)` for every word on every cold-cache text shape. Creating a `ShapePlan` parses the font's OpenType layout tables — several ms per call. `gpui`'s `LineLayoutCache` is frame-scoped; any message scrolled out of view has its layouts evicted. On scroll-back, all lines re-shape simultaneously.

**Fix:** `crates/cosmic-text-patched` adds a `VecDeque<(fontdb::ID, Direction, Script, ShapePlan)>` cache to `ShapeBuffer`, backported from `cosmic-text 0.17.1`. See ARCHITECTURE.md — "Patched / Vendored Dependencies" for full details and removal instructions.

**Rules that follow from this:**

- `render()` spans are useful for measuring re-render *frequency* (catching unnecessary `cx.notify()` calls), not shaping cost. Use `samply` for the latter.
- **Never hand a multi-kilobyte `SharedString` to a div child unless the message is likely to stay in view.** The collapse-by-default on `Thinking` blocks exists partly for this reason — a collapsed block renders only a header line, so only that line shapes on scroll-in instead of hundreds.
- When adding any new text-heavy view (log viewer, diff display, long node descriptions), default to collapsed or paginated to bound the cold-shape cost per scroll-in. The ShapePlan cache amortises the per-word plan cost but does not eliminate the per-line layout cost for lines that have never been seen before.
- **Do not mix large text rendering with `cx.notify()` hot paths.** Streaming tokens call `notify()` on the target `ChatMessageView` only; all sibling messages are not dirtied. If you restructure the streaming path so that a parent entity notifies, all visible chat messages will re-shape every token — catastrophic at 50 tok/s.
